"Content": "According to your needs \"status code 200, number of statistical log entries\", I analyzed this as a retrieval and analysis requirement. It requires retrieving logs with status code 200 and counting the number of log entries.\n\nBased on the field configuration of the Nginx log topic, the `status` field is of long data type and has statistics enabled. The following is the generated CQL statement:\n\n\\`\\`\\`sql\nstatus:200 | SELECT count(*) AS log_count\n\\`\\`\\`\n\n**Explanation:**\n1. **Retrieval condition**: `status:200` - retrieve logs with status code 200\n2. **SQL statement**: `SELECT count(*) AS log_count` - count the number of qualified logs\n3. **Verification result**: the statement passed validation\n\nSince this is a statistical query, the pipe character `|` is required to connect the retrieval condition and the SQL analysis statement. The statement uses `status:200` as the retrieval condition and then uses the `count(*)` function to count the number of log entries."
        },
        {
"Content": "Count 5xx again"
            "Role": "user"
        }
    ],
    "Stream": true,
    "Metadata": [
        {
            "Key": "topic_id",
            "Value": "xxxxxxxx-xxxx"
        },
        {
            "Key": "topic_region",
            "Value": "ap-guangzhou"
        }
    ]
}

